OS X Terminal config files for Lion (xterm-256color).

I just create symlinks to these files from my $HOME directory ("ln -s $HOME/code/dot_files/.inputrc ~" for example).

Terminal key setup (this makes bash, vim, and irssi work how I like):

  end               \033[4~
  home              \033[1~
  page down         \033[6~
  page up           \033[5~

  ctrl page up      \033[5;5~
  control page down \033[6;5~

  shift end         scroll to end of buffer
  shift home        scroll to beginning of buffer
  shift page down   scroll to next page in buffer
  shift page up     scroll to previous page in buffer

I also turn "Use option as meta key" on - the default meta key is the escape key.

Another possibility is to use \033[F for end and \033[H for home, and add something like the following to your .vimrc:

  nmap <esc>[H 0
  imap <esc>[H <esc>I
  cmap <esc>[H <home>
  nmap <esc>[F $
  imap <esc>[F <esc>A
  cmap <esc>[F <end>

Using .inputrc seemed cleaner.

